The paper discusses the construction of a global map of science based on aggregated journal-journal citations, which involves data analysis and visualization techniques. This falls under the scope of several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and sound (cs.SD). The paper also mentions the use of portfolio analysis, which could be related to topics in computer science such as machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM).
